## Surveyed paths

- context/HANDOFF.md — Active Workstreams section. Relevant: "Plans/Census/Mapping read-only per cuts D1/D2/D3" — this proposal explicitly lifts the D1 cut.
- context/CORE_MEMORY.md — rules: build to expected backend contract; new widgets must include registry integration + tests + real consumer; commit-hygiene split (src vs context); branch hygiene exception for /build-feature on dirty trees; DSL is canon.
- docs/spec/quotation/QuotationDomain.domain — Quote entity functions: `addPlan`, `updatePlan(plan)`, `removePlan(planNo)`. Precondition for all three: `isDraft`. addPlan/updatePlan additionally require `hasCensusFileFormat` — UI must surface this dependency (cannot add/edit plans until census file format is set).
- docs/spec/common/CommonData.data — DSL canonical shapes:
  - `Plan { planNo, planName?, products: list<PlanProduct>, rateCardFile, coverAmountFormula, freeCoverLimitFormula? }`
  - `PlanProduct { productCode, productName?, productType, benefits: list<PlanBenefit>, exclusions: list<PlanExclusion> }`
  - `PlanBenefit { code, name?, mandatory }`
  - `PlanExclusion { code, name? }`
  - `AmountFormula { type: AmountFormulaType, multiplicationFactor?, lookupTableJson?, memberAttributeName?, fixedAmount?, dmnTableFile? }`
- schemas/tabs/quote/plans.json — current key-value-grid extraction; to be rewritten.
- schemas/forms/edit-quote-policy-detail-form.json — reference for form schema conventions.
- src/components/widgets/data/CardGrid.tsx — stub already in place from setup step.
- src/components/registry/WidgetRegistry.tsx — `card-grid` already registered to the stub component.
- src/components/widgets/forms/formContainer/FieldRenderer.tsx — field-type registry; json-textarea field type will be added by PROP-0007 (separate workstream), so V1 of plan-edit-form will need plain textarea + manual JSON validation, or this lane adds json-textarea opportunistically.
- src/components/widgets/forms/OverlaidForm.tsx — modal form wrapper; receives `data` from `open-modal` rowData per registry inventory, but pre-fill into form fields is uncertain.
- src/lib/api/quotation.ts — existing API client; expected wrappers: addPlan / updatePlan / removePlan. Need to read to confirm.

## API endpoints (proxied to https://group-pas-dev.anairacloud.com)

- POST `/api/quotation/quotes/{id}/plans` — body: PlanRequest
- PUT `/api/quotation/quotes/{id}/plans/{planNo}` — body: PlanRequest (full replace)
- DELETE `/api/quotation/quotes/{id}/plans/{planNo}`
- GET `/api/quotation/quotes/{id}` — drives the page; `plans[]` is the array we iterate

## Known (locked)

1. Cards iterate `plans[]` from `GET /api/quotation/quotes/{id}`.
2. DSL data shapes for Plan / PlanProduct / PlanBenefit / PlanExclusion / AmountFormula are stable.
3. Edits are DRAFT-only (precondition `isDraft`). Maker role.
4. addPlan/updatePlan additionally require `hasCensusFileFormat` — the UI surfaces this as a disabled-with-tooltip when census file format is not set, per the existing precondition-tooltip pattern used by the pricing tab.
5. New widget `card-grid` already pre-registered to a stub. This run replaces the stub with the real implementation.
6. Proxy mode is live; no mock plumbing required.

## Ambiguous (needs user input)

1. **Per-card Edit modal pre-fill.** The Explore-agent inventory said "No pre-fill from entity context observed" — `open-modal` passes rowData to OverlaidForm but no clear plumbing turns rowData into pre-filled form-field values. Two options:
   - (A) **Wire pre-fill in this lane** — small addition to OverlaidForm / FormContainer to seed initial values from rowData. Slightly bigger PROP-0004 but ships full Edit affordance.
   - (B) **Ship cards + Add only**; defer per-card Edit to a follow-up (PROP-0009). User loses the inline edit but read-side gap is closed.
2. **Branch strategy.** /build-feature's rule says "feature branch on dirty tree", which would mean five separate branches across the 5 workstreams. CORE_MEMORY's general rule says "stay on current branch". The current branch is `feat/new-buisiness` (not main), tree is dirty from setup-lane + Lane A. Three options:
   - (A) Commit current dirty state first (Lane A's PROP-0006 work + setup-lane widget stubs), then run all 5 workstreams as sequential commits on `feat/new-buisiness`.
   - (B) Five feature branches off `feat/new-buisiness` HEAD (skill default).
   - (C) Single integration branch `feature/quote-detail-tabs-expansion` carrying all 5 sequentially.
3. **Plan-edit-form structured fields vs raw JSON.** Proposal says V1 uses raw JSON textareas for `productsJson` / `coverAmountFormulaJson`. Per CORE_MEMORY "build to expected real-backend contract" — raw JSON is honest about the API but bad UX. Alternatives:
   - (A) **Raw JSON V1, structured editor as PROP-0009** (current plan).
   - (B) **Structured editor now** — large addition; needs multi-row repeater widget. Outside the lane's stated scope.

